-- HMS Group Retreats to Four-Month Low as Profit Declines 51%
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-06-14T15:05:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/hms-group-retreats-to-four-month-low-as-profit-declines-51-.html
HMS Group, a Russian pump
manufacturer, fell to a four-month low as first-quarter profit
tumbled 51 percent from a year earlier.  HMS Group dropped 2.2 percent to $4.45, the lowest intraday
level since Feb. 2 as of 2:55 p.m. in  London .  First-quarter income fell 51 percent to 485 million rubles
($14.9 million), according to an e-mailed statement. Revenue
rose 4 percent to 7.31 billion rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
